  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "[The documentation of `library SafeMath`](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/utils/math/SafeMath.sol#L12-L13) states:\r\n> NOTE: `SafeMath` is no longer needed starting with Solidity 0.8. The compiler now has built in overflow checking.\r\n\r\nThis is not entirely accurate IMO.\r\n\r\nConsider the following scenario:\r\n- We decide to upgrade to solc 0.8\r\n- We have a function which consists of many native operations, but only a handful of `SafeMath` operations\r\n\r\nInstead of splitting that function into several blocks of 'checked' code and 'unchecked' code, it is cleaner to just scope the entire function code within an `unchecked` block, which means that the `SafeMath` library remains useful in such cases.\r\n\r\nThanks",
